<title>USA: Oracle sets 3-for-2 stock split.</title>
<headline>Oracle sets 3-for-2 stock split.</headline>
<dateline>REDWOOD CITY, Calif. 1997-07-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>Oracle Corp said Monday it has set a three-for-two stock split of its outstanding shares of common stock.</p>
<p>The stock split will be effected in the form of a stock dividend and will entitle each stockholder of record on August 1 to receive three shares for every two shares of Oracle common stock held on the record date. Oracle said it will pay cash in lieu of fractional shares.</p>
<p>The stock dividend will be paid on August 15.  Oracle currently has about 652,624,000 shares of common stock outstanding.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
